  <entry>
    <title>Incident Response Phases</title>
    <link href="https://notes.samfeldstein.xyz/notes/incident-response-phases/" />
    <updated>2025-06-13T15:16:12Z</updated>
    <id>https://notes.samfeldstein.xyz/notes/incident-response-phases/</id>
    <content type="html">
&lt;html&gt;&lt;head&gt;&lt;/head&gt;&lt;body&gt;&lt;ol&gt;&lt;li&gt;Preparation&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Detection and analysis&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Containment, eradication, and recovery&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Post-incident activity&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ol&gt;&lt;h2&gt;Preparation&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p&gt;Take measures to prevent incidents.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;h2&gt;Detection and analysis&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p&gt;Analyze an incident to learn about its severity.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;h2&gt;Containment, eradication, and recovery&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p&gt;Stop the incident from affecting other systems, eliminate it, and recover the affected systems.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;h2&gt;Post-incident activity&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p&gt;Report findings to prevent similar future incidents.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/body&gt;&lt;/html&gt;
</content>
  </entry>
